-- Government Stimulus Package Could Total $60 Billion, Kyodo News Reports
-- B y   F e r g u s   M a g u i r e
-- 2010-10-05T21:04:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/government-stimulus-package-could-total-60-billion-kyodo-news-reports.html
The Democratic Party of Japan may
today decide to increase the size of a planned stimulus package
by 200 billion yen to about 5 trillion yen ($60 billion), Kyodo
News said, citing unidentified party sources.  The Cabinet plans to endorse the package on Oct. 8, the
report said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fergus Maguire at 
 fmaguire@bloomberg.net  